      <div xml:id="Aink8-kilavi">
        <p type="edition"> ituvumatu. </p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en"> </p>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="Aink8">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>          vāḻi yātaṉ vāḻi yaviṉi</l>
<l>          yaracumuṟai ceyka kaḷavil lākuka</l>
<l>          veṉavēṭ ṭōḷē yāyē yāmē</l>
<l>          yalaṅkuciṉai māat taṇimayi lirukkum</l>
<l>          pūkkaña lūraṉ cūḷivaṇ	</l>
<l>          vāyppa tāka veṉavēṭ ṭēmē.</l>
        </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>          'Long live Ātan! Long live Aviṉi! </l>
<l>          May the king deliver justice! May there be no theft!' </l>
<l>          That's what our mother wants. As for us: </l>
<l>          'The promises of the man from the village teeming with flowers,</l>
<l>          where picturesque peacocks perch in the mango trees with swaying branches: </l>
<l>          May they come true here!' — that's what we want.</l>
          
          


        </lg>
      </div>
